[Auction "E"]
1NT 2D 2NT pass 3C pass 3D pass 3H pass 3NT pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "80d2438f1ee0a6a729d409ba64648a5856c1afdd7d61a1ce68558601d5a59003"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/lebensohl"]
[Student "S"]
{Partner's 2NT bid requests that you bid 3\C, so you do. He next says 3\D.  

Partner's bid is game-forcing Stayman, but with a \D stopper (SLOW SHOWS). Holding 4 cards in each Major you bid up-the-line, 4\H. Partner now bids 3NT.  

Partner would not have asked for a 4-card Major unless he held one himself. Since it wasn't \Hs it must be the other one. You bid 4\S.}

